Paper: hep-th/9204007

Date: 1992-04-03

Title: Anomalous Transformation in Supersymmetric Yang-Mills Theory

Authors: H.Itoyama and B.Razzaghe-Ashrafi

Comments: 8 pp

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B291 (1992) 268-272

An ``anomalous'' supersymmetry transformation of the gaugino axial current isgiven in supersymmetric Yang-Mills theory. The contact term is computed toone-loop order by a gauge-invariant point-splitting procedure. We reexamine thesupercurrent anomaly in this method.